Package main.record

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IRecord
    The IRecord interface is used for testing and in the building of our main.record classes, this is a representation of all our action records.
    IRecordBuilder
    Interface for all records that need to be built from input lines
    IRecordVisitor
    Common implementation of the visitor pattern, needed interface A visitor for each type of main.record
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ActionRecord
    This is an abstraction of all our action records
    MarketPriceRecord
    Record represents the market price
    PerformanceRecord
    This class represents a performance multiplier line
    RecordCalculatorVisitor
    The main.record visitor visits all main.record types and for the most part adds them to a set list for calculations once all records have been visited per user
    RecordComparer  
    SaleRecord
    This class represents a vested option sale line
    VestRecord
    This class represents a vested option line
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    RecordAction
    Enum to represent the possible actions the input from our text file can have
